and the winner's
whoever's not dead?

772
00:47:34,951 --> 00:47:36,145
No. No one's gonna die.

773
00:47:36,219 --> 00:47:37,584
There's only one thing
that works with Taha...

774
00:47:37,654 --> 00:47:39,053
and if we use it,
it will give us time.

775
00:47:39,122 --> 00:47:40,749
- What's that?
- His curiosity.

776
00:47:42,358 --> 00:47:43,825
Who's this cop
he's talking about?

777
00:47:43,893 --> 00:47:45,224
Mm-mmm.

778
00:47:45,294 --> 00:47:46,522
What is this?
Whenever I ask a question...

779
00:47:46,596 --> 00:47:48,325
I get a "Mm-mmm."

780
00:47:48,398 --> 00:47:49,695
Hell of a vocabulary.

781
00:47:49,766 --> 00:47:50,994
OK, find out everything
about that guy.

782
00:47:51,067 --> 00:47:52,295
I mean everything.

783
00:47:52,368 --> 00:47:54,598
And I want him here,
not at the morgue.

784
00:47:54,671 --> 00:47:56,138
I'll be right back.

785
00:47:58,441 --> 00:48:00,705
Count me out. Too risky.

786
00:48:00,777 --> 00:48:02,039
You're dead
if you do it alone.

787
00:48:02,111 --> 00:48:03,544
I've always worked alone,
and I'm still around...

788
00:48:03,613 --> 00:48:05,638
so fuck off, Jack.

789
00:48:05,715 --> 00:48:07,512
I know Taha's place
like the back of my hand...

790
00:48:07,583 --> 00:48:09,551
all the exits, even the one I dug out myself.

791
00:48:09,619 --> 00:48:11,712
Dude, I'm very happy for you.
I hope your hands didn't hurt.

792
00:48:11,788 --> 00:48:13,449
I know where the bomb is!

793
00:48:13,523 --> 00:48:14,785
You'll never find it
without me.

794
00:48:15,925 --> 00:48:16,983
A couple of minutes ago,
you didn't even know...

795
00:48:17,060 --> 00:48:18,186
there was a bomb.

796
00:48:18,261 --> 00:48:19,626
What is this bullshit?

797
00:48:19,696 --> 00:48:21,493
Taha's got a safety vault
for valuable things...

798
00:48:21,564 --> 00:48:22,724
and I know how to get in.

799
00:48:22,799 --> 00:48:24,096
How do you know
he put it in there?

800
00:48:24,167 --> 00:48:25,634
Where's he gonna put it,
in the kitchen?

801
00:48:27,303 --> 00:48:28,531
OK, here's the deal.

802
00:48:28,604 --> 00:48:30,902
I set you free, and you shut up
and do what I say, OK?

803
00:48:30,973 --> 00:48:32,440
No, I've got another deal.

804
00:48:32,508 --> 00:48:33,998
You shut up,
pray my sister's alive.

805
00:48:34,077 --> 00:48:35,942
If you behave,
I'll get your bomb.

806
00:48:36,012 --> 00:48:38,207
Now uncuff me
before we're in deep shit up to our necks.

807
00:48:41,918 --> 00:48:42,976
Deal.

808
00:48:48,024 --> 00:48:49,116
Is this guy the cop?

809
00:48:49,192 --> 00:48:50,989
Wow, what a sense
of deduction, K2. I'm impressed.

810
00:48:51,060 --> 00:48:52,152
That's very funny.

811
00:48:52,228 --> 00:48:55,061
If Taha doesn't finish you off,
the pleasure will be all mine.

812
00:48:55,131 --> 00:48:56,428
Come on, let's go.
Follow us.

813
00:48:56,499 --> 00:48:58,865
And no bullshit.
We're the nervous kind.

814
00:49:14,150 --> 00:49:15,344
Hey!

815
00:49:15,418 --> 00:49:16,851
Guard duty isn't for sleeping.

816
00:49:16,919 --> 00:49:18,250
Sorry, but I dozed off.

817
00:49:18,321 --> 00:49:19,948
- Where is he?
- In the back.

818
00:49:27,096 --> 00:49:28,791
Did you feed him?

819
00:49:28,865 --> 00:49:30,230
He eats all the time.

820
00:49:35,805 --> 00:49:38,865
I got some work for you,
so you can stretch your legs a bit.

821
00:49:47,083 --> 00:49:49,313
They could wipe out a city
with all this shit.

822
00:49:54,223 --> 00:49:56,453
That's the van they transported
the bomb in it.

823
00:49:56,526 --> 00:49:57,993
At least we're sure it's here.

824
00:50:06,035 --> 00:50:07,969
Stay here, I'll pick you up on the way out.

825
00:50:08,037 --> 00:50:09,402
Very funny.

826
00:50:25,888 --> 00:50:27,685
Seems you got a new pal,
a fucking cop.

827
00:50:27,757 --> 00:50:29,418
He's no friend of mine.

828
00:50:29,492 --> 00:50:30,686
He's the only one
that can defuse...

829
00:50:30,760 --> 00:50:32,819
- the bomb you stole.
- The only one?

830
00:50:32,895 --> 00:50:35,022
When the countdown ends,
everything goes within 8 kilometers.

831
00:50:35,097 --> 00:50:36,655
And you, of course,
have come here to save us.

832
00:50:36,732 --> 00:50:37,994
There's a code
that will stop the timer.

833
00:50:38,067 --> 00:50:40,160
It will save more than
two million people.

834
00:50:40,236 --> 00:50:41,498
The state sends us
a brave cop...

835
00:50:41,571 --> 00:50:43,004
to save us from a nasty bomb...

836
00:50:43,072 --> 00:50:45,336
that without our pal here
is gonna go boom.

837
00:50:45,408 --> 00:50:47,569
Great story.
Thanks, Superman.

838
00:50:47,643 --> 00:50:49,110
But let me be honest with you.

839
00:50:49,178 --> 00:50:52,170
You see, we weren't planning
on hanging onto your bomb.

840
00:50:52,248 --> 00:50:53,237
So you want it back?

841
00:50:53,316 --> 00:50:54,874
Yeah.

842
00:50:54,951 --> 00:50:56,282
How much?

843
00:50:58,521 --> 00:50:59,681
If I don't punch in the code
within an hour...

844
00:50:59,755 --> 00:51:00,847
the bomb will explode.

845
00:51:00,923 --> 00:51:02,015
I know it will explode.
So what?

846
00:51:02,091 --> 00:51:03,183
It's no concern of mine...

847
00:51:03,259 --> 00:51:04,590
as long as it's not where I live.

848
00:51:04,660 --> 00:51:06,150
But if you don't want it
to blow up where you live...

849
00:51:06,229 --> 00:51:07,890
well, like they say,
you better cough up a little...

850
00:51:07,964 --> 00:51:09,659
It'll kill millions
of innocent lives.

851
00:51:09,732 --> 00:51:11,791
Ah, but they should have
thought of that before...

852
00:51:11,868 --> 00:51:14,234
when they made it,
for example, huh?

853
00:51:14,303 --> 00:51:15,429
So, how much?

854
00:51:19,675 --> 00:51:21,905
A million.
Euros.

855
00:51:21,978 --> 00:51:24,606
I have a million on my right
for openers.

856
00:51:24,680 --> 00:51:26,307
Do I hear a higher offer? K2?

857
00:51:28,451 --> 00:51:30,681
Two million. I have
a two million bid on my left.

858
00:51:30,753 --> 00:51:31,811
So, who will double that?

859
00:51:34,023 --> 00:51:36,389
- Here.
- Nice kid. Four million.

860
00:51:36,459 --> 00:51:37,687
Four million.
Four million on my right.

861
00:51:37,760 --> 00:51:38,818
How far you gonna go?

862
00:51:38,895 --> 00:51:40,795
When you think our lives
aren't worth the price...

863
00:51:40,863 --> 00:51:43,093
tell me,
and I'll stop bidding.

864
00:51:46,202 --> 00:51:48,227
Ten? Ten million on my left.

865
00:51:48,304 --> 00:51:50,465
Good. Now things
are getting a little lively.

866
00:51:51,807 --> 00:51:53,775
Well, Blues Brothers, ten million.

867
00:51:53,843 --> 00:51:56,073
There's only one of its kind.
You want it or not?

868
00:51:58,147 --> 00:52:00,479
Well, since you got
no more to fork up...

869
00:52:00,549 --> 00:52:01,777
ten million's the price.

870
00:52:01,851 --> 00:52:04,285
Ten million going once.

871
00:52:04,353 --> 00:52:05,581
Ten million going twice.

872
00:52:10,026 --> 00:52:12,017
- Twenty.
- Whoa.

873
00:52:12,094 --> 00:52:14,358
Handsome bid...
in the eleventh hour, too.

874
00:52:15,598 --> 00:52:16,724
K2? Hmm?

875
00:52:16,799 --> 00:52:19,267
No, that's good.
He can have it.

876
00:52:19,335 --> 00:52:22,668
Twenty million. Wrap it up.

877
00:52:24,040 --> 00:52:25,302
Twenty million
for two million victims.

878
00:52:25,374 --> 00:52:26,807
That's about ten Euros a head.

879
00:52:26,876 --> 00:52:28,434
Price of a couple of burgers.

880
00:52:30,246 --> 00:52:31,372
Cash or what?

881
00:52:31,447 --> 00:52:33,711
Transfer. Forget cash.

882
00:52:33,783 --> 00:52:35,717
There's not time to go
to the bank and come back.

883
00:52:35,785 --> 00:52:37,446
The bomb will explode before.

884
00:52:37,520 --> 00:52:41,547
Jamel, give him
our account number in the Bahamas.

885
00:52:47,229 --> 00:52:48,321
First let me see the bomb.

886
00:52:48,397 --> 00:52:51,161
Oh, that's funny. I was sure
you were gonna ask me that.

887
00:52:51,233 --> 00:52:52,495
Help yourself.

888
00:52:58,607 --> 00:53:00,199
Your bomb didn't have a launcher.

889
00:53:00,276 --> 00:53:02,574
It's lucky I always keep
some equipment around here.

890
00:53:02,645 --> 00:53:04,510
We found a Russian launcher.
We sort of modified it.

891
00:53:04,580 --> 00:53:06,138
Your baby's ready to go.

892
00:53:06,215 --> 00:53:08,979
As for the direction I decide
to point it, I'll let you guess.

893
00:53:25,968 --> 00:53:28,368
You satisfied?
You've seen your bomb?

894
00:53:28,437 --> 00:53:30,837
Now make the transfer.

895
00:53:37,580 --> 00:53:39,946
You see, Leito,
I learned something from you.

896
00:53:40,016 --> 00:53:41,847
Now it's me
who's one step ahead.

897
00:53:51,694 --> 00:53:53,662
Get me Krüger. It's urgent.

898
00:54:39,742 --> 00:54:43,007
8-4-7-3-5.

899
00:54:43,079 --> 00:54:45,673
Zulu, Zulu, Fox, Delta, Charlie.

900
00:54:45,748 --> 00:54:47,079
How much has to be transferred?

901
00:54:47,149 --> 00:54:48,673
Twenty million Euros.

902
00:54:49,718 --> 00:54:52,209
Are you sure the bomb is there?

903
00:54:52,288 --> 00:54:54,188
It's right in front of me.

904
00:54:54,256 --> 00:54:56,190
I can even read
the 48 minutes left on the screen.

905
00:54:57,927 --> 00:54:59,690
Captain, we don't have
that kind of budget.

906
00:54:59,762 --> 00:55:01,161
You've got to manage otherwise.

907
00:55:01,230 --> 00:55:02,527
I'm sorry.

908
00:55:11,107 --> 00:55:12,199
OK, I'll hold.

909
00:55:12,274 --> 00:55:14,936
They're doing the transfer.

910
00:55:15,010 --> 00:55:16,307
OK, thank you, Colonel.

911
00:55:17,646 --> 00:55:18,738
It's done.

912
00:55:18,814 --> 00:55:20,304
Twenty million Euros
are in your account.

913
00:55:20,382 --> 00:55:22,873
I'll get started on the bomb.

914
00:55:22,952 --> 00:55:24,613
Our deal's not quite finished.

915
00:55:24,687 --> 00:55:26,655
Jamel, call the Bahamas,
make sure the money's arrived.

916
00:55:26,722 --> 00:55:28,019
That's what I'm doing.

917
00:55:35,631 --> 00:55:37,496
The bank doesn't open
for a half an hour.

918
00:55:37,566 --> 00:55:39,261
Let's hope it opens on time.

919
00:55:39,335 --> 00:55:41,360
If you two don't mind,
go wait in the next room.

920
00:55:42,905 --> 00:55:44,702
Get over there. On your knees.

921
00:55:44,773 --> 00:55:46,400
Face the wall.
Hands behind your head.

922
00:55:49,979 --> 00:55:52,846
Yoyo, watch these two
until you hear from me.

923
00:55:58,621 --> 00:55:59,918
What do we do now?

924
00:55:59,989 --> 00:56:01,820
Hey, don't forget
we did what you wanted.

925
00:56:01,891 --> 00:56:04,155
If we'd have played it cool,
we wouldn't be here.

926
00:56:04,226 --> 00:56:06,057
Yeah, and if your buddies
made the transfer...

927
00:56:06,128 --> 00:56:07,152
we'd already be out of here.

928
00:56:07,229 --> 00:56:08,890
Already dead, you mean.

929
00:56:08,964 --> 00:56:11,432
You don't suppose Taha
would've let us out of here.

930
00:56:11,500 --> 00:56:13,798
We'll never know,
since your pals refused to pay up.

931
00:56:15,304 --> 00:56:17,898
Now at least you know
how much your life is worth.

932
00:56:17,973 --> 00:56:19,201
Huh! Joking.

933
00:56:19,275 --> 00:56:21,106
To them, I'm not worth anything at all.

934
00:56:26,749 --> 00:56:28,512
Damien.

935
00:56:28,584 --> 00:56:30,017
There's something not right
about this whole thing.

936
00:56:30,085 --> 00:56:31,177
What do you mean?

937
00:56:31,253 --> 00:56:33,278
Something, I don't know what.

938
00:56:33,355 --> 00:56:35,550
They lose a bomb
like we lose our keys.

939
00:56:35,624 --> 00:56:37,251
They want to get it back,
but they don't want to pay.

940
00:56:37,326 --> 00:56:38,418
Look, when it comes
to blackmail...

941
00:56:38,494 --> 00:56:39,552
they're very particular.

942
00:56:39,628 --> 00:56:41,994
Hey, Supercop,
why are you defending them?

943
00:56:42,064 --> 00:56:43,497
I'm not, but there are values...

944
00:56:43,566 --> 00:56:45,431
real values.

945
00:56:45,501 --> 00:56:47,799
The same ones I thought
you defended, too.

946
00:57:04,887 --> 00:57:06,377
How much time we got?

947
00:57:11,493 --> 00:57:13,825
37 minutes.

948
00:57:13,896 --> 00:57:15,090
Wouldn't hurt
to have an idea.

949
00:57:15,164 --> 00:57:17,189
Yeah, it wouldn't hurt.

950
00:57:17,266 --> 00:57:19,826
Well, I think I've got one.

951
00:57:19,902 --> 00:57:22,200
Well?

952
00:57:22,271 --> 00:57:23,966
Remember the tunnel
I told you about?

953
00:57:24,039 --> 00:57:25,131
The one that you dug out
with your teeth?

954
00:57:25,207 --> 00:57:26,799
That's right.

955
00:57:26,875 --> 00:57:28,069
It starts in the toilet...

956
00:57:28,143 --> 00:57:29,235
