What's happening?

994
00:59:25,894 --> 00:59:27,486
Why don't you answer
when I call you?

995
00:59:27,563 --> 00:59:29,224
Uh, we were in a tunnel.

996
00:59:29,298 --> 00:59:31,061
I would like to know what the fuck
you're talking about!

997
00:59:31,133 --> 00:59:33,328
Well, it was because
of those two assholes...

998
00:59:33,402 --> 00:59:34,528
that got away through the tunnel.

999
00:59:34,603 --> 00:59:35,865
We tried to catch up
with them...

1000
00:59:35,938 --> 00:59:37,405
- but then the walkie-talkies...
- Hold on a second.

1001
00:59:37,473 --> 00:59:38,633
Repeat that once more.

1002
00:59:38,707 --> 00:59:40,641
Leito and the cop, they...

1003
00:59:51,019 --> 00:59:54,113
Jamel!
What about the transfer?

1004
00:59:59,061 --> 01:00:00,289
We got problems, Taha.

1005
01:00:00,362 --> 01:00:02,091
- He was bluffing.
- Yeah.

1006
01:00:02,164 --> 01:00:03,392
You know,
I should have known!

1007
01:00:03,465 --> 01:00:05,399
You can't trust a cop never...

1008
01:00:05,467 --> 01:00:07,196
even with a gun to his head.

1009
01:00:07,269 --> 01:00:09,499
But he'll pay for this, the bastard!

1010
01:00:09,571 --> 01:00:10,833
I'm going to detonate the bomb!

1011
01:00:10,906 --> 01:00:13,272
Taha... Taha,
I think you had better sit down.

1012
01:00:17,212 --> 01:00:18,804
They used the Bahamas
account number to move in...

1013
01:00:18,881 --> 01:00:20,849
on all of the numbered
bank accounts, and...

1014
01:00:20,916 --> 01:00:22,747
they cleaned them all out.

1015
01:00:22,818 --> 01:00:23,944
What's our...

1016
01:00:25,220 --> 01:00:27,188
Bahamas, Riyadh, Karachi...

1017
01:00:27,256 --> 01:00:28,348
all of them, even London.

1018
01:00:28,424 --> 01:00:30,324
- Nothing. Zero.
- What?

1019
01:00:32,594 --> 01:00:34,687
But how's that possible?

1020
01:00:34,763 --> 01:00:37,197
If I ever learn that,
I'll be the king of the world.

1021
01:00:39,234 --> 01:00:40,201
In the meantime...

1022
01:00:40,269 --> 01:00:41,463
this dumb little accountant...

1023
01:00:41,537 --> 01:00:43,300
is going back home.

1024
01:00:48,076 --> 01:00:49,805
Excuse me.

1025
01:00:57,886 --> 01:00:59,217
Hey, Taha, if you're broke...

1026
01:00:59,288 --> 01:01:00,812
then how the fuck
are you going to pay us this week?

1027
01:01:13,836 --> 01:01:15,565
I got cash in the safe
downstairs.

1028
01:01:15,637 --> 01:01:17,002
No one's about
to rip that off.

1029
01:01:18,140 --> 01:01:19,664
K2, your piece.
Hand it over.

1030
01:01:24,546 --> 01:01:25,638
K2, give it to me, huh?

1031
01:01:38,660 --> 01:01:41,823
You are a bunch
of fucking shitheads.

1032
01:02:07,256 --> 01:02:08,848
What do we do now, K2?

1033
01:02:16,265 --> 01:02:19,462
First, we better find Leito
and that cop.

1034
01:02:19,535 --> 01:02:21,503
OK, move out, everyone.

1035
01:03:22,598 --> 01:03:24,225
We better separate!

1036
01:04:57,559 --> 01:04:58,856
Out of the way! Move!

1037
01:05:01,930 --> 01:05:03,124
Police!

1038
01:05:48,944 --> 01:05:51,139
How long
before this bomb goes off?

1039
01:05:51,213 --> 01:05:52,305
Ten minutes.

1040
01:05:52,380 --> 01:05:53,904
And you're sure
you can defuse it.

1041
01:05:53,982 --> 01:05:55,415
Yeah. What's more,
I'm the only one.

1042
01:05:55,484 --> 01:05:59,011
Well, you go and stop it,
and Leito stays with us.

1043
01:05:59,087 --> 01:06:00,452
No, I need him
to come with me.

1044
01:06:00,522 --> 01:06:01,580
No can do.

1045
01:06:01,656 --> 01:06:03,783
OK. Leito and me
will stay here...

1046
01:06:03,859 --> 01:06:05,190
and you defuse the bomb.
How's that?

1047
01:06:05,260 --> 01:06:06,921
You better go.
You've only got nine minutes.

1048
01:06:10,893 --> 01:06:12,451
OK, you both go.

1049
01:06:12,528 --> 01:06:13,825
I'll wait for you down below.

1050
01:06:13,896 --> 01:06:15,659
You gotta come down
sooner or later, huh?

1051
01:06:15,731 --> 01:06:16,698
If I do the job,
I bet even you...

1052
01:06:16,766 --> 01:06:18,097
will be glad to see a cop's face.

1053
01:06:18,167 --> 01:06:19,225
Hmm.

1054
01:06:48,931 --> 01:06:51,058
What the hell is that?

1055
01:06:51,133 --> 01:06:52,259
A present from Taha.

1056
01:06:53,936 --> 01:06:55,563
Let me handle this.
I love presents.

1057
01:07:46,989 --> 01:07:48,354
Hey, Mongo! You ready now...

1058
01:07:48,424 --> 01:07:49,652
for me to teach you
a thing or two?

1059
01:08:27,463 --> 01:08:29,090
Hey! He's all yours.

1060
01:08:42,077 --> 01:08:44,511
Nice going!
Where did you learn that?

1061
01:08:44,580 --> 01:08:45,740
In a cookbook or official manual...

1062
01:08:45,815 --> 01:08:47,043
I don't remember.

1063
01:09:14,510 --> 01:09:16,842
It's all over, Lola, It's all over.

1064
01:09:19,515 --> 01:09:21,483
No, sorry,
but it's far from over.

1065
01:09:24,920 --> 01:09:26,387
Fuck it,
I can't get through.

1066
01:09:30,192 --> 01:09:32,023
OK, got it.

1067
01:09:32,094 --> 01:09:33,584
Don't worry.
He's an expert at the cuffs.

1068
01:09:33,662 --> 01:09:34,788
He'll get them off you.

1069
01:09:38,534 --> 01:09:40,092
- Hello?
- Captain Tomaso.

1070
01:09:40,169 --> 01:09:41,864
I've got the bomb in front of me.
I need the code.

1071
01:09:41,937 --> 01:09:43,063
Where are you now?

1072
01:09:43,138 --> 01:09:44,901
The bomb's in front of me
with 31/2 minutes left.

1073
01:09:44,974 --> 01:09:46,305
Give me the code,
and we'll talk later.

1074
01:09:46,375 --> 01:09:47,569
Where are you? The exact spot.

1075
01:09:47,643 --> 01:09:50,203
On the roof of a building
in Barrio 13.

1076
01:09:50,279 --> 01:09:51,405
Do you want
the weather forecast as well?!

1077
01:09:51,480 --> 01:09:53,744
Good work, Tomaso.
We're all very proud of you.

1078
01:09:53,816 --> 01:09:55,078
Thanks, but time's running out.

1079
01:09:55,150 --> 01:09:57,380
9-2-9-3...

1080
01:09:57,453 --> 01:09:58,852
9-2-9-3...

1081
01:09:58,921 --> 01:10:01,287
3-7-0-9-B-13.

1082
01:10:01,357 --> 01:10:02,585
7-0-9-B-13.

1083
01:10:02,658 --> 01:10:04,285
I'll call you back
if I'm still alive.

1084
01:10:12,635 --> 01:10:14,569
B-13? Like Barrio 13?

1085
01:10:14,637 --> 01:10:16,332
- Yeah.
- Doesn't it seem strange...

1086
01:10:16,405 --> 01:10:17,804
that the bomb's code is Barrio 13...

1087
01:10:17,873 --> 01:10:20,034
92, 93, the two zones we're in?

1088
01:10:20,109 --> 01:10:22,407
Just coincidence.

1089
01:10:22,478 --> 01:10:23,911
Damien, wait! Hold on.

1090
01:10:23,979 --> 01:10:25,071
If the bomb wasn't scheduled
to come here...

1091
01:10:25,147 --> 01:10:26,808
why the hell does it have
the same number as this barrio?

1092
01:10:26,882 --> 01:10:29,578
Look, whatever it is,
I've got to stop it, OK?

1093
01:10:29,652 --> 01:10:31,244
Damien, listen.
What if it's the reverse?

1094
01:10:31,320 --> 01:10:32,252
The reverse of what?

1095
01:10:32,321 --> 01:10:34,255
You detonate the bomb
with the code instead.

1096
01:10:34,323 --> 01:10:35,950
Why send me, then,
if they wanted the fucking thing...

1097
01:10:36,025 --> 01:10:37,822
to explode in the first place?
Explain that!

1098
01:10:37,893 --> 01:10:39,360
So it blows up right here
where they want...

1099
01:10:39,428 --> 01:10:40,725
the center of Barrio 13.

1100
01:10:40,796 --> 01:10:41,990
"Give me the exact spot."

1101
01:10:42,064 --> 01:10:43,793
Wasn't that what
your boss asked?

1102
01:10:43,866 --> 01:10:45,527
Yeah, but that's
a security measure!

1103
01:10:45,601 --> 01:10:46,795
It's a trap, Damien,
I'm sure!

1104
01:10:46,869 --> 01:10:48,461
Get off my back
and let me work!

1105
01:10:55,511 --> 01:10:57,103
I've already saved your life once,
so trust me!

1106
01:10:57,179 --> 01:10:59,443
I'm a soldier!
I've got a mission to do!

1107
01:11:44,159 --> 01:11:45,251
Cut this shit out, Leito!

1108
01:11:45,327 --> 01:11:46,385
In one minute,
we're all going to...

1109
01:11:46,462 --> 01:11:47,520
Open your eyes, Damien!

1110
01:11:47,596 --> 01:11:49,029
Nobody gives a shit
about this barrio.

1111
01:11:49,098 --> 01:11:50,690
Twenty years, and they can't
solve the problem.

1112
01:11:50,766 --> 01:11:51,858
They built a wall around us...

1113
01:11:51,934 --> 01:11:53,663
now they're going
to clean it out for good.

1114
01:11:53,736 --> 01:11:55,203
How come there are
no civil servants here?

1115
01:11:55,270 --> 01:11:57,170
No post office or schools,
and just by chance...

1116
01:11:57,239 --> 01:11:58,570
the police station
was shut down.

1117
01:11:58,640 --> 01:12:00,505
But the bomb was stolen, Leito.
They didn't make that up.

1118
01:12:00,576 --> 01:12:02,635
Oh, yeah, the bomb was attacked
by some bad guys, right?

1119
01:12:02,711 --> 01:12:04,611
Yeah.

1120
01:12:04,680 --> 01:12:05,669
That's the story
they told you, huh?

1121
01:12:05,748 --> 01:12:06,840
- Yeah.
- Then tell me why...

1122
01:12:06,915 --> 01:12:08,780
just before we saw the van,
it was intact.

1123
01:12:08,851 --> 01:12:10,148
Where were the signs
of an explosion...

1124
01:12:10,219 --> 01:12:11,709
of a smashed-in door?

1125
01:12:11,787 --> 01:12:12,754
Maybe it was a different one.

1126
01:12:12,821 --> 01:12:14,345
It was the same,
and you know damn well.

1127
01:12:14,423 --> 01:12:15,515
And once they were sure...

1128
01:12:15,591 --> 01:12:17,058
the bomb was on
the inside of Barrio 13...

1129
01:12:17,126 --> 01:12:18,525
and that it wasn't
going anywhere...

1130
01:12:18,594 --> 01:12:20,357
they got their best pit bull
to set it in motion.

1131
01:12:20,429 --> 01:12:22,056
And you really accomplished that mission.

1132
01:12:22,131 --> 01:12:23,189
You stopped Taha
from dumping it...

1133
01:12:23,265 --> 01:12:24,357
so it's all for us.

1134
01:12:45,654 --> 01:12:46,746
It can't be possible, Leito!

1135
01:12:46,822 --> 01:12:48,119
You don't kill
two million people...

1136
01:12:48,190 --> 01:12:49,248
'cause you can't
solve their problems!

1137
01:12:49,324 --> 01:12:50,416
No? They murdered six million...

1138
01:12:50,492 --> 01:12:52,460
because none of them
were blond with blue eyes!

1139
01:13:09,845 --> 01:13:11,403
Sorry, Leito.

1140
01:13:26,695 --> 01:13:28,094
Sorry.

1141
01:13:28,163 --> 01:13:29,187
Get off me!

1142
01:13:29,264 --> 01:13:31,323
I prefer dying for my brother's dumb ideas
than for yours.

1143
01:14:02,898 --> 01:14:04,195
It's over?

1144
01:14:04,266 --> 01:14:05,995
This time it really is over.

1145
01:14:10,973 --> 01:14:12,736
It's not over.

1146
01:14:29,625 --> 01:14:31,354
I told you that even you...

1147
01:14:31,426 --> 01:14:32,654
would be glad to see my face.

1148
01:14:33,896 --> 01:14:35,386
You got five minutes
to leave here.

1149
01:14:35,464 --> 01:14:37,432
Can I take a souvenir?

1150
01:14:38,700 --> 01:14:40,258
Yeah, be my guest.

1151
01:14:49,244 --> 01:14:51,712
Uh-huh.

1152
01:14:53,215 --> 01:14:55,012
Thank you. Nothing yet.

1153
01:14:55,083 --> 01:14:57,449
Jesus Christ, it's well over an hour
that we've been waiting.

1154
01:14:57,519 --> 01:14:58,850
And if by tonight nothing happens,
then what?

1155
01:14:58,921 --> 01:15:00,320
I've no idea, Corsini.
For Christ's sake...

1156
01:15:00,389 --> 01:15:02,721
it's supposed to explode
and that's that.

1157
01:15:02,791 --> 01:15:03,883
What's going on?

1158
01:15:03,959 --> 01:15:05,187
Sounds like a fight.

1159
01:15:05,260 --> 01:15:06,227
Go and have a look!

1160
01:15:20,275 --> 01:15:21,572
There.
Mission accomplished.

1161
01:15:21,643 --> 01:15:23,634
Well, not quite.
At the last minute...

1162
01:15:23,712 --> 01:15:25,270
we couldn't remember the code.

1163
01:15:25,347 --> 01:15:26,712
- But we both tried, didn't we?
- Mm-hmm.

1164
01:15:26,782 --> 01:15:27,874
But it's my fault, totally.

1165
01:15:27,950 --> 01:15:29,349
It was me
who forgot the numbers.

1166
01:15:29,418 --> 01:15:31,079
- You remember yours, right?
- Oh, yeah.

1167
01:15:31,153 --> 01:15:32,245
Hey, he's incredible.

1168
01:15:32,321 --> 01:15:34,482
We made an absolutely
fantastic team, you know?

1169
01:15:34,556 --> 01:15:36,581
And without Leito,
I'd be dead now.

1170
01:15:36,658 --> 01:15:38,148
OK, let's have it.

1171
01:15:38,227 --> 01:15:41,287
92, 93.

1172
01:15:41,363 --> 01:15:43,490
- Wow, like the two zone numbers.
- Yeah.

1173
01:15:43,565 --> 01:15:45,123
That's wild, eh?

1174
01:15:45,200 --> 01:15:46,997
A coincidence.

1175
01:15:47,069 --> 01:15:48,297
Now, we got 7-0-9.

1176
01:15:48,370 --> 01:15:50,395
Easy to remember,
that's today's date.

1177
01:15:50,472 --> 01:15:53,703
7-0-9. September 7...

1178
01:15:53,775 --> 01:15:55,106
end of the summer holidays.

1179
01:15:55,177 --> 01:15:56,769
Practical, eh?
A bomb explodes on the day...

1180
01:15:56,845 --> 01:15:58,506
you know everyone's
around for sure...

1181
01:15:58,580 --> 01:16:01,014
and you get rid of
all the scum in one shot.

1182
01:16:01,083 --> 01:16:02,482
If I'm mistaken, please stop me.

1183
01:16:02,551 --> 01:16:05,577
Now then, the code.

1184
01:16:05,654 --> 01:16:08,179
I think that I've got the rest of it.

1185
01:16:08,257 --> 01:16:11,454
B13. Like Barrio 13.

1186
01:16:11,526 --> 01:16:14,461
How could I forget?

1187
01:16:14,529 --> 01:16:15,791
Why don't I give you
the honor of finishing?

1188
01:16:15,864 --> 01:16:18,128
Are you telling me you plan
on blowing up this bomb here in Paris?!

1189
01:16:18,200 --> 01:16:20,634
I'm sorry, but I thought the code was
to defuse the bomb.

1190
01:16:20,702 --> 01:16:22,602
You mean that if I punch it in,
it'll do the opposite...

1191
01:16:22,671 --> 01:16:24,832
Stop playing the fool, Tomaso!
You know perfectly well!

1192
01:16:24,906 --> 01:16:26,635
No, I don't. Explain it to me.
I want to know why...

1193
01:16:26,708 --> 01:16:28,835
Barrio 13 is uncontrollable.
It costs a fortune to the state.

1194
01:16:28,910 --> 01:16:29,968
The taxpayers are worried.

1195
01:16:30,045 --> 01:16:32,605
Worried, frightened, and fed up
with paying for such scum!

1196
01:16:32,681 --> 01:16:34,444
So we clean it out with a bomb?

1197
01:16:34,516 --> 01:16:37,144
Yes. It's not very democratic,
but it solves all the problems.

1198
01:16:37,219 --> 01:16:39,119
Except one. Yours, sir.

1199
01:16:40,422 --> 01:16:41,446
No, I beg of you! Please!

1200
01:16:41,523 --> 01:16:42,615
Look, why don't we clean up everything?

1201
01:16:42,691 --> 01:16:43,783
Do you want us all killed?!

1202
01:16:43,859 --> 01:16:46,384
You should have thought
of that when you built it!

1203
01:16:46,461 --> 01:16:48,156
No!

1204
01:17:01,243 --> 01:17:02,870
You really thought I was going
to go through with it.

1205
01:17:02,944 --> 01:17:04,468
Why? For revenge?

1206
01:17:04,546 --> 01:17:07,674
No, you don't always need
violence to solve problems.

1207
01:17:07,749 --> 01:17:09,478
There are
more democratic ways.

1208
01:17:10,852 --> 01:17:12,717
Look out of the window,
and smile.

1209
01:17:15,724 --> 01:17:17,214
Was the sound OK?

1210
01:17:19,394 --> 01:17:20,725
What are you plotting, Tomaso?

1211
01:17:20,796 --> 01:17:23,356
I'm doing my job, sir.
You know what my job is?

1212
01:17:23,432 --> 01:17:26,128
I see that laws are obeyed.
Obeyed by everyone.

1213
01:17:26,201 --> 01:17:27,668
I make sure
that no one forgets that.

1214
01:17:27,736 --> 01:17:29,533
That's my job...
no more, no less.

1215
01:17:29,604 --> 01:17:32,937
Now, if you still
don't understand...

1216
01:17:33,008 --> 01:17:34,839
you can see it all on network TV.

1217
01:17:34,910 --> 01:17:36,844
As well as internet reservations.

1218
01:17:36,912 --> 01:17:38,038
You can also purchase
your ticket...

1219
01:17:38,113 --> 01:17:40,843
on the train from a conductor.

1220
01:17:40,916 --> 01:17:43,510
No tickets are as yet available
at ticket windows

1221
01:17:43,585 --> 01:17:45,678
and this may continue for some time.

1222
01:17:45,754 --> 01:17:48,188
For rail companies,
it's impossible to estimate...

1223
01:17:48,256 --> 01:17:50,554
when the computer breakdown
will be repaired.

1224
01:17:50,625 --> 01:17:53,492
As you know,
it has now been twenty-four hours...

